{
  "text": "In the breeding seasons of 2013 and 2014, we blood sampled 3-day-old chicks from 116 nests (see [CITATION_1] for details). From these blood samples, erythrocyte telomere length was measured by in-gel TRF [CITATION_2] . Variation in chick telomere length was not explained by year, brood size or by offspring sex, hatching order and body mass [CITATION_3] .",
